This plan also considers the importance of cross-cutting issues that relates to each of the sub­sectors such as:
* Climate Change & Resilience;
* Vulnerable groups;
* Human and Institutional Capacity;
* Promotion and Dissemination of Information;
* Energy Efficiency across the sector; and
* Gender Equity.

The Long Term Outcomes outlined within the SDS are as follows:
* Renewable energy investment and generation increased;
* Electricity supply access and reliability improved;
* Road transport energy efficiency policy planning improved;
* Petroleum supply, management and safety improved;
* Climate and Disaster resilience management integrated into energy planning and

The five (5) End of Sector Plan Outcomes that has been identified and are targeted to be achieved within the timeframe of the energy sector plan 2017-2022 are:
* Renewable Energy Increased;
* Electricity Services Improved;
* Energy Efficient Transport Sector;
* Management of Petroleum Products Enhanced;
* Coordination of Energy Sector Improved.

The important cross-cutting issues considered when formulating policy for each Sub-sector are:
* Climate change & Disaster Resilience;
* Vulnerable Groups;
* Human and Institutional Capacity;
* Promotion and Dissemination of Information;
* Energy Efficiency across the sector;
* Gender Equity.
